data.name: Kodak Vigilant
data.description: This utterly beautiful old Kodak Six-16 camera is just dying for a special space in your bookshelves. Made in the 1930s, It is barely weathered, with the outer black casing still in great condition. I have no idea if it is working or not, but all components seem to be functional. It is in very good vintage condition. The black bellows are still in great shape. Nothing can detract from the awesomeness of this camera as a display piece, it truly is magnificent, especially for a photography lover like myself! Also, this sweet vintage camera comes with the original rustic leather carrying case, which is very cool!
